Concept:     Transformer
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Attention-based model processing sequences in parallel
Year:        2017
Researchers: Vaswani et al.
Applications:LLMs, vision models, protein folding
Related:     GPT, BERT, attention mechanism

Concept:     Diffusion Model
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Learns to reverse a noise-adding process for generation
Year:        2020
Researchers: Ho et al.
Applications:Image/video/audio generation (Stable Diffusion)
Related:     DDPM, score matching, noise schedule

Concept:     Backpropagation
Category:    Training
Definition:  Computes gradients via chain rule through network layers
Year:        1986
Researchers: Rumelhart/Hinton
Applications:Training all neural networks
Related:     Gradient descent, automatic differentiation

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Diminishing Returns
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: More of one input eventually yields smaller output increases
Formula:    Marginal product falls
Economist:  Turgot/Marshall
Example:    More workers in fixed factory eventually get in each other's way

Concept:    Central Bank
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government institution managing currency, money supply, interest rates
Formula:    Taylor Rule for interest rates
Economist:  John Taylor
Example:    US Federal Reserve raised rates to 5.25% in 2023 to fight inflation

Concept:    Gini Coefficient
Category:   Statistics
Definition: Measures income inequality from 0 (equal) to 1 (one person has all)
Formula:    G = 1 - 2∫L(x)dx
Economist:  Corrado Gini
Example:    USA Gini ~0.41; Denmark ~0.29; South Africa ~0.63

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

Concept:      Determinism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   All events are causally determined by prior events and natural laws
Philosopher:  Laplace/Spinoza
Example:      If universe were rewound exactly, every event would repeat identically

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Maximize pleasure minimize pain across all sentient beings
Philosopher:  Jeremy Bentham
Example:      Felicific calculus: measure units of pleasure and pain

